      "id": "https://www.myeastkootenaynow.com/56323/news/transit/summer-traffic-in-the-kootenays-increases-risk-for-roadside-workers/",
      "url": "https://www.myeastkootenaynow.com/56323/news/transit/summer-traffic-in-the-kootenays-increases-risk-for-roadside-workers/",
      "title": "Summer traffic in the Kootenays increases risk for roadside workers : My East Kootenay Now",
      "content_html": "Photo supplied by Canada Safety Council. Transit 2 min.read # Summer traffic in the Kootenays increases risk for roadside workers My East Kootenay Now Staff By My East Kootenay Now Staff June 28, 2026 FacebookXReddItWhatsAppEmail With the July 1 holiday marking the start of the busy summer travel season, drivers across the Kootenays will encounter more orange cones, construction crews and roadside workers as highways and local roads see increased traffic. Whether heading to a campground, lake, hiking trail or ferry, drivers face added pressure from busy schedules, road delays and long trips.",
